💫 ✨Embrace life's full potential! 🙏 

 Living life to its fullest potential is a wonderful philosophy to embrace. Here's a brief reminder of how you can achieve it:

Embrace your health: Prioritize your well-being by adopting a healthy lifestyle.
This includes eating nutritious foods, getting regular exercise, managing stress, and getting enough rest.

Get fit: Engage in physical activities that you enjoy, whether it's going to the gym, doing yoga, dancing, hiking, or any other form of exercise. Staying active not only keeps you physically fit but also has numerous mental and emotional benefits.

Help others: Show kindness and compassion to others. Small acts of kindness can have a significant impact on someone's day and foster a sense of fulfillment in you.

Pursue your passions: Discover and follow your passions and interests. Engaging in activities you love can bring joy and a sense of purpose to your life.

Set goals: Define clear and achievable goals for yourself. Working toward these objectives can provide motivation and a sense of accomplishment.

Cultivate positive relationships: Surround yourself with supportive and positive people who encourage you to grow and become the best version of yourself.

Practice gratitude: Focus on the positive aspects of your life and express gratitude for the blessings you have. Gratitude can foster happiness and contentment.

Remember that life is a journey, and it's okay to face challenges along the way. Embrace them as opportunities for growth and learning. Happy Friday, and here's to a fulfilling and purposeful life! 💪😊

Happy Friday!! ❤️🙏❤️🙏❤️🙏❤️🙏❤️

🌟 Daily reminder my friends... 
Results take time!

Do you ever feel discouraged when you don't see immediate results from your efforts? Do you sometimes question if you're on the right track or if you're wasting your time? It's a natural feeling, but I'm here to remind you that nothing happens overnight, and results do happen when you take action.

🌟✨ Success and progress require consistent effort and hard work. It's easy to get caught up in the instant gratification culture of today, where everything seems to be at our fingertips. But the reality is, real change takes time and dedication.

🤔 🎯 Think about your goals and aspirations. Do you want to lose weight, start a business, learn a new skill, or improve a relationship? Whatever it is, know that it won't happen overnight. But every small step you take, every action you make, is a step closer to achieving your goal.

Remember that success is not a straight line. It's filled with ups and downs, twists and turns. You may encounter setbacks and obstacles along the way, but don't let that deter you from your path. Keep pushing forward, stay committed, and have faith that your efforts will pay off.

🏋️ 🏋️ So, take action today. Start small and keep going. Be patient and persistent. Don't let the fear of failure or the desire for instant gratification hold you back from achieving your dreams. Remember that nothing happens overnight, but results do happen when you take action.

🙌♥️ You have the power to create the life you want. It's up to you to make it happen. So, take that first step, and keep moving forward. You've got this!

😋 Strawberry - Chocolate 🍫 Greek Yogurt Bark 

Ingredients:

3 cups whole-milk plain Greek yogurt

¼ cup pure maple syrup or honey

1 teaspoon vanilla extract

1 ½ cups sliced organic strawberries

¼ cup mini chocolate chips

Directions :

1-Line a large rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper.

2-Stir yogurt, maple syrup (or honey) and vanilla in a medium bowl. Spread on the prepared baking sheet into a 10-by-15-inch rectangle. Scatter the strawberries on top and sprinkle with chocolate chips.

3-Freeze until very firm, at least 3 hours. To serve, cut or break into 32 pieces.

Equipment :

Large rimmed baking sheet, parchment paper

To make ahead
Freeze airtight between sheets of parchment for up to 1 month.

Nutrition Facts (per serving)
34 Calories
1g Fat
4g Carbs 
2g Protein

😋 High Protein Snack - Greek yogurt, peanut butter Greek yogurt, powdered peanut butter. 

Mix 1 cup (227 g) unflavored 2% milk Greek yogurt, 2 teaspoons powdered peanut butter, 1 teaspoon unsweetened cocoa powder, 1 teaspoon stevia, 1/4 teaspoon (¼ teaspoon) vanilla extract together until smooth.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon chopped 85% chocolate or your favorite chopped chocolate bar. Nutritionals are figured using 85% chocolate.

Notes: Sometimes I will squirt a little whipped cream on top of the yogurt before we sprinkle it with chocolate. It’s a naughty pleasure!

The recipe is written for plain powdered peanut better. If you can find powdered chocolate peanut butter, you can leave out the cocoa powder.

The "Gecko Pose" is a yoga posture that targets various muscle groups, enhances flexibility, and contributes to overall mobility. Here's a flow and the associated benefits for your mobility.

In this case here. I'm teaching my client to do a modify version of the Gecko Pose with a body flow which will help him to increase his upper body strength and great overall mobility and flexibility exercise.

Here are some of the benefits associated with this movements.

Hip Flexibility: Gecko Pose and body flow targets the hip flexors, promoting increased flexibility in the hips, which is beneficial for activities requiring hip mobility.

Improved Thoracic Rotation: The twisting aspect of Gecko Pose enhances thoracic spine mobility, contributing to a more flexible and agile upper body.

Ankle Mobility: The dynamic movement involved in transitioning into and out of Gecko Pose helps to improve ankle mobility, crucial for overall stability.

Enhanced Core Strength: Engaging the core muscles during the pose builds strength, stability, and control, supporting better overall mobility.

Shoulder Opening: The option to bind in Gecko Pose stretches and opens the shoulders, promoting better range of motion in the shoulder joints.

Incorporating the Gecko Pose and body flow into your regular yoga practice can contribute to increased mobility, flexibility, and strength, making it a valuable addition to your movement routine.

Up your protein intake with this delicious recipe!
High Protein Almond Pancakes 🥞😋 😋
Amazing option for your breakfast or quick snack! 

Ingredients:

1 cup almond flour

1 cup milk (dairy or plant-based)

2 large eggs

2 scoops of your favorite protein powder

1 teaspoon baking powder

Pinch of salt

Optional: 1 tablespoon honey or maple syrup for sweetness

Cooking spray or a bit of butter for the pan

Instructions:

Blend Almond Flour: In a mixing bowl, combine the almond flour, milk, eggs, protein powder, baking powder, and salt. Add honey or maple syrup if desired, for a touch of sweetness.

Let the Batter Rest: Allow the batter to rest for 5-10 minutes to ensure a smooth consistency.

Preheat the Pan: Heat a non-stick skillet or griddle over medium heat. Lightly coat it with cooking spray or a small amount of butter.

Cook the Pancakes: Pour 1/4 cup portions of batter onto the hot pan. Cook until bubbles form on the surface, then flip and cook the other side until golden brown.

Serve: Stack the almond flour pancakes on a plate and top with your favorite nut butter, sliced fruits, or a drizzle of honey. Enjoy these high-protein pancakes for a tasty and nutritious breakfast after your workout!

Uncover the nutritional wonder of beef, lamb, and 
steak. Vaccenic acid (TVA) is a fatty acid that can be found in meat and dairy products. It is a type of naturally occurring trans fat, and its potential benefits and impacts on health have been a subject of research. While the research is ongoing and some findings may vary, here are some potential benefits associated with trans-vaccenic acid:

Converted to Conjugated Linoleic Acid (CLA):
Trans-vaccenic acid can be converted into conjugated linoleic acid (CLA) in the body. CLA has been studied for its potential health benefits, including anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties.

Potential Anti-Cancer Properties:
Some studies suggest that CLA, derived from trans-vaccenic acid, may have anti-cancer properties. It has been explored for its potential role in preventing certain types of cancers.

💪Metabolic Effects:
Research indicates that CLA, formed from TVA, might influence body composition by reducing body fat and increasing lean muscle mass. This has led to investigations into its potential role in weight management.

❤️ Cardiovascular Health:
Some studies have explored the impact of CLA on cardiovascular health. It's been suggested that CLA may have positive effects on lipid profiles, potentially contributing to heart health.

🎯 Immunomodulatory Effects:
CLA, originating from trans-vaccenic acid, has been studied for its potential immunomodulatory effects. It may play a role in supporting the immune system.

🧠 Brain Health: limited research suggests that CLA might have neuroprotective effects and could contribute to brain health. However, more research is needed in this area.

It's important to note that while there may be potential benefits associated with trans-vaccenic acid and its benefits. As with any dietary component, moderation and a balanced diet are key, and individual responses to dietary factors can vary. Consulting with a healthcare professional or a registered dietitian is recommended for personalized advice based on specific health conditions and goals.

Simple and delicious drumstick 🍗 recipe using Adobo Ole and Herbs de Provence: 🌿 

Ingredients:
- Chicken drumsticks
- Adobo Ole spice blend
- Herbs de Provence

Instructions:
1. Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).
2. Pat the drumsticks dry with paper towels.
3. In a bowl, mix Adobo Ole spice blend, Herbs de Provence, little bit of olive oil to create a marinade.
4. Coat the drumsticks with the marinade, ensuring they are evenly covered.
5. Place the drumsticks on a baking sheet
6. Bake in the preheated oven for 45 to 60 minutes, or until the chicken is golden brown and cooked through.
7. For extra flavor, baste the drumsticks with the juices halfway through the cooking time.
8. Once done, let them rest for a few minutes before serving.

I usually cook with skin for better flavor 😋 once it's done cooking. I remove the skin 👍I know.. Some people wants that crispy skin so bad lol 😂 🤣 🤣
